title: Google\Cloud\LifeSciences\V2beta\DelayedEvent
name: DelayedEvent
description:
An event generated whenever a resource limitation or transient error delays execution of a pipeline that was otherwise ready to run.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.lifesciences.v2beta.DelayedEvent

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.cause
params.description: A textual description of the cause of the delay. The string can change without notice because it is often generated by another service (such as Compute Engine).

params.name: data.metrics
params.description: If the delay was caused by a resource shortage, this field lists the Compute Engine metrics that are preventing this operation from running (for example, CPUS or INSTANCES). If the particular metric is not known, a single UNKNOWN metric will be present.
